📌 Business Objective:

  • We are looking to understand why employees are leaving , identify key drivers of attrition , and build a forecasting model that predicts monthly employee turnover. This will help us better plan for hiring, manage costs, and reduce churn.

🔍 Key Requirements:

  • Perform Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) to uncover patterns in attrition.
  • Identify top factors influencing employee turnover .
  • Build a time-series forecasting model to predict future attrition rates.
  • Create visualizations and dashboards to communicate findings.
  • Provide actionable insights for HR leadership.

Loop Through Categorical Variables → Countplots¶

In [48]:
# set style
sns.set(style='whitegrid')

for col in categorical_cols:
    plt.figure(figsize=(15,5))
    
#     Distribution of Categories
    plt.subplot(1,2,1)
    sns.countplot(data=analyzable_df, x=col)
    plt.title(f"Distribution of {col}")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.show()
    
#     Attrition by Category
    plt.figure(figsize=(18,5))
    plt.subplot(1,2,2)
    sns.countplot(data=analyzable_df, x=col, hue="Attrition")
    plt.title(f"Attrition by {col}")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

Loop Through Numeric Variables → Boxplots¶

In [51]:
for col in numeric_cols:
#     Distribution
    plt.figure(figsize=(15,5))
    plt.subplot(1,2,1)
    sns.histplot(data=analyzable_df, x=col, kde=True)
    plt.title(f"Distribution of {col}")
    plt.show()
    
#     Attrition vs variable
    plt.figure(figsize=(18,5))
    plt.subplot(1,2,2)
    sns.boxplot(data=analyzable_df, x="Attrition", y=col)
    plt.title(f"Attrition vs {col}")
    plt.show()
